Fall of Rebel Angels. Dürer School Drawing (fragment) in Museum of Fine Arts, Boston for Window of Fall of Rebel Angels in Landauerkloster, Nürnberg, publ. by [Campbell] Dodgson O.M. Dr., [= 'School of Dürer. The Fall of the Rebel Angels". Fragment of a Cartoon for Stained Glass, Museum of Fine Art, Boston', in: Old Master Drawings], V, Sept.1930, pl. 23, text p. 42 f. The windows now in Schloss-Museum, Berlin, publ. by Hermann Schmitz, in the catal. of the glass paintings in the Museum [= Die Glasgemälde des Königlichen Kunstgewerbemuseums in Berlin, 2 vols., Berlin: Bard], (1913) The window to which the drawing relates on pl. 240. Dodgson:"Though there is no doubt that the whole design must have been made by Dürer this fragment can hardly itself be attributed to the masters hand...'

The windows now in Schloss-Museum, Berlin, publ. by Hermann Schmitz, in the catal. of the glass paintings in the Museum [= Die Glasgemälde des Königlichen Kunstgewerbemuseums in Berlin, 2 vols., Berlin: Bard], (1913) The window to which the drawing relates on pl. 240. Dodgson:""Though there is no doubt that the whole design must have been made by Dürer this fragment can hardly itself be attributed to the masters hand...'</content>
